===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The point of [[junction]] between two things, in particular a support, that [[abut#English|abuts]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|engineering|architecture}} The solid portion of a structure that supports the lateral pressure of an [[arch]] or [[vault]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|engineering}} A [[construction]] that supports the ends of a [[bridge]]; a structure that anchors the cables on a [[suspension bridge]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1959|month=May|title=Talking of Trains: Bethnal Green alterations|journal=Trains Illustrated|page=236|text=Each of the bridges consists of six separate girder spans on brick '''abutments'''.}}
# {{lb|en|meteorology}} The part of a [[valley]] or [[canyon]] wall against which a [[dam]] is constructed.
#: Heavy rains have caused the dam's '''abutments''' to seep, raising concern over possible dam failure.
# Something that [[abut]]s, or on which something abuts. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The state of [[abutting]].
# {{lb|en|architecture}} That [[element]] that shares a common boundary or surface with its neighbor.
# {{lb|en|dentistry}} The tooth that supports a [[denture]] or [[bridge]].
# A [[fixed]] [[point]] or [[surface]] where [[resistance]] is [[obtained]].
#: The [[fulcrum]] acted as an '''abutment'''.

